The paper deals with the performance analysis of asynchronous strategies for solving distributed optimization and adaptation problems over networks. This involves analyzing the convergence rate and steady-state deviation of the mean-square-error. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) which deals with the analysis and design of systems that involve feedback and control. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the transmission and processing of information over networks. Machine learning (cs.LG) is also relevant as the paper deals with learning and adaptation over networks. Networked systems (cs.NI) is another relevant category as the paper deals with networks and their behavior. Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis (cs.MA) as it derives analytical expressions for the mean-square convergence rate and steady-state mean-square-deviation.
